Directory structure:

sbert_search/
├── CMakeLists.txt
├── README.md
├── include/
│   ├── hnswlib/          # vendored header-only HNSWlib
│   ├── SBertGGML.hpp
│   ├── BertIndex.hpp
│   ├── ShardedIndex.hpp
│   ├── BertIndexManager.hpp
│   ├── HnswConfig.hpp
│   └── HNSWIndexCache.hpp
│   └── Util.hpp
├── src/
│   ├── SBertGGML.cpp
│   ├── BertIndex.cpp
│   ├── ShardedIndex.cpp
│   ├── BertIndexManager.cpp
│   ├── Util.cpp
│   └── main.cpp
└── tests/
    └── run_test.sh


Final notes & tips

CMake: your CMakeLists.txt should compile all .cpp in src/ and include include/. Link to bert and ggml and -framework Accelerate on macOS, plus pthread if needed.

Adjustments: depending on your hnswlib version and BERT C API signatures, you might need tiny name tweaks (e.g., cur_element_count vs getCurrentElementCount()); I tried to use common names but adapt if your headers differ.

Testing: after building, run the test script (tests/run_test.sh)




